CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 12, 1958, pg. 28 reads: "Fetching, Indeed was Jean Carpenter, who spent Easter Sunday night at the New Nixon, attending the D.I.'s smart affair. Her gown featured lace and fox fur."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Jean Carpenter wearing sleeveless, lace, v-neck dress and fur stole, seated on leaf patterned settee, in the New Nixon with sign behind her inscribed "The New Nixon Presents, Now, a Craig Daye Production", for D.I.'s "Breath of Spring" revue
